<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="320" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,726,751]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body medium. Fastigium verticis narrower than scapus, moderately sloping anteriorly, dorsally furrowed, sinuate upper edge in lateral view, separated from fastigium frontis. Pronotum with anterior margin approximately straight, posterior margin broadly rounded, three transverse sulci distinct and medial carina interrupted by second sulcus, which Y-shaped; paranota longer than deep, anterior margin concave slightly, ventral and posterior margins moderately rounded, humeral sinus distinct. Procoxae unarmed; all femora with dorsum smoothly and longitudinal groove on venter, profemur with 
<number box="[889,931,907,931]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
minute spines on ventro-internal margin, mesofemur with 
<number box="[348,391,943,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
spines on ventro-external margin, postfemur with 
<number box="[985,999,943,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="4.0">4</number>
spines on ventro-external margin, all genicular lobes without spines; protibiae with internal tympanum covered by a conchate fold, external tympanum free, widened at and abruptly constricted below tympana. Tegmen nearly equal width throughout, apex rounded, extending beyond apex of postfemur, Rs branching before the middle of radius, 
<number box="[1044,1058,1051,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="2.0">2</number>
branches; hind wings longer than tegmina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Stridulatory area of left tegmen oval, 
<quantity box="[625,726,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.29" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="4.29">4.29 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[798,899,1122,1147]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.62" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="2.62">2.62 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[978,1060,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[212,1374,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[212,1374,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male stridulatory area of left tegmen and mirror of right tegmen of Mirollia species: A – B. M. hexapinna; C – D. M. hainani; E – F. M. multidentatus; G – H. M. maculosus sp. nov.; I – J. M. caligata; K – L. M. obscuripennis; M – N. M. amplecta sp. nov.; O – P. M. unispina sp. nov.; Q. M. lanceolata (stridulatory area)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235804/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[1031,1060,1123,1147]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
M); stridulatory file on underside of left tegmen concave and slightly curved, 
<quantity box="[654,756,1159,1183]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="0.98">0.98 mm</quantity>
long; teeth faint in basal fifth; with 
<number box="[1173,1242,1159,1183]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="90.5" valueMax="93.0" valueMin="88.0">88–93</number>
teeth, (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1410,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[165,1420,193,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[165,1421,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stridulatory file on underside of male left tegmen of Mirollia species: A. M. amplecta sp. nov.; B. M. unispina sp. nov.; C. M. fallax (from Banlao, Cangyuan, Yunnan); D. M. multidentatus (from Jiangfengling, Ledong, Hainan); E. M. deficientis (from Hupingshan, Shimen, Hunan)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235798/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Figs. 
<number box="[1395,1410,1159,1183]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[151,178,1195,1219]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="11.0">11</number>
O); mirror oval, 
<quantity box="[362,462,1194,1219]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.60 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[532,632,1194,1219]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.76" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" unit="mm" value="2.76">2.76 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[707,789,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[212,1374,193,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[212,1374,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male stridulatory area of left tegmen and mirror of right tegmen of Mirollia species: A – B. M. hexapinna; C – D. M. hainani; E – F. M. multidentatus; G – H. M. maculosus sp. nov.; I – J. M. caligata; K – L. M. obscuripennis; M – N. M. amplecta sp. nov.; O – P. M. unispina sp. nov.; Q. M. lanceolata (stridulatory area)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235804/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[760,789,1195,1219]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
N). Tenth abdominal tergite with posterior margin slightly concave; epiproct short, tongue-shaped, dorsally furrowed; cerci long, but not reaching apex of subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male abdominal apex, cerci and subgenital plate of Mirollia species: A – C. M. maculosus sp. nov.; D – F. M. petiolulata sp. nov.; G – I. M. composita; J – L. M. hainani; M – O. M. amplecta sp. nov.; P – R. M. unispina sp. nov.; S. M. terminalis sp. nov. A, D, G, J, M, P, S. abdominal apex in lateral view (S. in dorsal-lateral view); B, E, H, K, N, Q. apex of subgenital plate in apical view; C, F, I, L, O, R. apex of cercus in apical view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235801/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[215,229,1267,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
M), baso-internal side expanded, posteriorly narrowing; strongly curved inwards in apical quarter; apex compressed laterally, acute (
<figureCitation box="[475,544,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male abdominal apex, cerci and subgenital plate of Mirollia species: A – C. M. maculosus sp. nov.; D – F. M. petiolulata sp. nov.; G – I. M. composita; J – L. M. hainani; M – O. M. amplecta sp. nov.; P – R. M. unispina sp. nov.; S. M. terminalis sp. nov. A, D, G, J, M, P, S. abdominal apex in lateral view (S. in dorsal-lateral view); B, E, H, K, N, Q. apex of subgenital plate in apical view; C, F, I, L, O, R. apex of cercus in apical view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235801/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[529,544,1303,1327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
O); phallus with two pair of sclerites: lateral sclerites bent inwards, basal part wide, distal part rather narrow; medial sclerites small, apex rounded and denticulated (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1211,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1553,1575]" captionTargetBox="[163,1426,193,1527]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1532]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12. Male abdominal apex, cerci, subgenital plate and phallus of Mirollia species: A. M. amplecta sp. nov.; B. M. unispina sp. nov.; C – E. M. acutilobata sp. nov.; F – G. M. maculosus sp. nov.; H – K. M. petiolulata sp. nov. A. right medial sclerite and lateral paired sclerites of phallus in apical view; B. medial and lateral sclerites of phallus in lateral view; C, H. abdominal apex in dorsal view; D. lateral sclerite of phallus in lateral view; E, K. medial sclerite of phallus in lateral view; F, I. abdominal apex in lateral view; G, J. cerci and subgenital plate in apical view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235806/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[1182,1211,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Subgenital plate curved dorsally before middle; basal part broad, medial area nearly equal width with apical part, posterior margin longitudinally split into two wide lobes (
<figureCitation box="[606,673,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1869,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1848]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male abdominal apex, cerci and subgenital plate of Mirollia species: A – C. M. maculosus sp. nov.; D – F. M. petiolulata sp. nov.; G – I. M. composita; J – L. M. hainani; M – O. M. amplecta sp. nov.; P – R. M. unispina sp. nov.; S. M. terminalis sp. nov. A, D, G, J, M, P, S. abdominal apex in lateral view (S. in dorsal-lateral view); B, E, H, K, N, Q. apex of subgenital plate in apical view; C, F, I, L, O, R. apex of cercus in apical view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235801/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
Fig. 
<number box="[658,673,1411,1435]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
N).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[199,269,1446,1470]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Color.</emphasis>
Body yellowish green. Pronotum with brown dots on disc and in paranota; a large brown spot occupies stridulatory area of left tegmen; numerous red dots on abdominal tergites; tibial tympana with brown conchate fold and lateral black stripes on basal dorsum; cerci with dark brown apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" box="[199,415,1554,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis box="[199,291,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male. Body: 13.0– 
<number box="[698,747,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="13.5">13.5</number>
; body with wings: 
<number box="[986,1101,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="26.0" valueMax="26.5" valueMin="25.5">25.5–26.5</number>
; pronotum: 
<number box="[1248,1336,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="3.2" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.3</number>
; tegmen length: 
<number box="[245,293,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="18.5">18.5</number>
–20.0; tegmen width: 
<number box="[567,655,1627,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="3.2" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.3</number>
; hind wing: 
<number box="[822,937,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="24.0" valueMax="24.5" valueMin="23.5">23.5–24.5</number>
; profemur: 
<number box="[1086,1122,1627,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="2.8">2.8</number>
–3.0; mesofemur: 
<number box="[1344,1432,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="4.75" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.3">4.3–5.2</number>
; postfemur: 
<number box="[279,315,1662,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" value="9.5">9.5</number>
–10.0.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="320" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is derived from Latin ‘amplecta’ = to embrace; it refers to lateral sclerites of phallus with distal part long and bent inwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,618,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1770,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species differs from known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1089,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Mirollia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[997,1089,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="320">Mirollia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of characteristic lateral sclerites of phallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
